title: Card terminal - button grayed out on POS
text: If the card terminal works, the light is on, it is connected to the POS, but you still can't access it from the POS, check Adv. Configuration in DdDAdmin on the POS (password: ddd+2016). 1. Click screen with wrench button 2. Choose Store, then machine, then click Change this machine only 3. Scroll down to Adv. configuration 4. If the majority of the fields are grayed out, enter the password ddd+2016 at the top and press Enter. 5. Scroll down to the UseTerminal field. 6. If UseTerminal is 0, then change to 1 7. Scroll down to the bottom and press save 8. Return to sale window and cancle sale. 9. Type reload in Sales Assistant field and press green button.
description:
If the card terminal works, the light is on, it is connected to the POS, but you still can't access it from the POS, check Adv. Configuration in DdDAdmin on the POS (password: ddd+2016). 


1. Click screen with wrench button

 


2. Choose Store, then machine, then click Change this machine only

 


3. Scroll down to Adv. configuration

 


4. If the majority of the fields are grayed out, enter the password ddd+2016 at the top and press Enter.


5. Scroll down to the UseTerminal field.

 

 

 

6. If UseTerminal is 0, then change to 1


7. Scroll down to the bottom and press save

 

8. Return to sale window and cancle sale.


9. Type reload in Sales Assistant field and press green button.

title: Card terminal - reconsiliate
text: Reconsiliation of the card terminal can be done from DdD POS. Log in, click on Shortcuts, choose Configure terminal and choose Reconsiliation If the card terminal says that you need to get the card agreements, this you have to do on the card terminal itself. Ask the Sales Clerk to swipe the merchant card (it's usually located underneath the terminal) Press 1 for Business Agreement Press 1 to retrieve agreements
description:
Reconsiliation of the card terminal can be done from DdD POS. 

Log in, click on Shortcuts, choose Configure terminal and choose Reconsiliation 

  

 

  

If the card terminal says that you need to get the card agreements, this you have to do on the card terminal itself. 

Ask the Sales Clerk to swipe the merchant card (it's usually located underneath the terminal)

title: Card terminal - won't connect to POS (German RIAB customers)
text: When a German customer gets a new card terminal, the following change has to be made to get the POS to communicate with the new terminal: 1. Open POS/Program/bin/Debug/Printer/Configuration/ESC Koder.txt 2. Scroll down to [GermanBankingConfig] 3. Change Port to Com1 (if different) 4. Change StopBit to 2 (if different) 5. Restart POS If it still doesn't work, repeat above steps and set Stopbit to 1.
description:
When a German customer gets a new card terminal, the following change has to be made to get the POS to communicate with the new terminal: 

  

  1. 1. Open POS/Program/bin/Debug/Printer/Configuration/ESC Koder.txt 

  1. 2. Scroll down to [GermanBankingConfig] 

  1. 3. Change Port to Com1 (if different) 

  1. 4. Change StopBit to 2 (if different) 

  1. 5. Restart POS 

  

If it still doesn't work, repeat above steps and set Stopbit to 1.

title: Card terminal - ERROR: 2011 ERR_SEND_LOW_LEVEL_FAIL
text: We have experienced "ERROR: 2011" errors on the old POS systems when they get a new Lane 3000 Dankort terminal. The error may occur because the driver is not installed on the POS for the new Lane 3000 terminals and the terminal is typically set to Com port 8. The Com Port should be set to 20(Check Device manager) Before installing the driver again, try Configure Terminal->Reconciliation (Konfigurer Terminal->Afstemning) The guide of how to install the driver (again) can be found here: https://k3support.freshdesk.com/a/solutions/articles/103000262325?lang=en

title: Installing Lane3000 cardterminal
text: When the customer calls to have their new Lane3000 cardterminal installed follow these steps. First ask them to check if the USB is properly connected. If you cannot see the terminal in Device Manager, this might be the problem. Inform them that a restart of the pc will happen, and this process can take up to 10mins where they can't use the POS Start by downloading the driver from: https://ingenico.com/en/resources/ingenico-usb-driver-application-and-installation-guide Close the DdDPos and start the installation. It should start with asking you if you want to uninstall the old driver. Press yes to this - after this is done it will ask for a reboot of the pc. Press reboot now. -IMPORTANT- When this pc starts up again after this reboot, it might start on a completely white screen (or the chosen wallpaper) with nothing else. This is just windows trying to identify the USB driver for the terminal. Just wait a few minutes and the installer will show up for the terminal. Follow the steps in the installer when you see this screen fill it out as shown here Press next and finish the installation. When installation is finished icons and start menu should reappear on the pc. Open DdDPos Login as a sales person Press shotcuts followed by configure terminal In the new window start with "download card agreements", if that succeeds run "reconciliation" if this succeds the card terminal should be ready for use. If this does not work, send to hardware
description:
When the customer calls to have their new Lane3000 cardterminal installed follow these steps.


First ask them to check if the USB is properly connected. If you cannot see the terminal in Device Manager, this might be the problem.

Inform them that a restart of the pc will happen, and this process can take up to 10mins where they can't use the POS

Start by downloading the driver from:

https://ingenico.com/en/resources/ingenico-usb-driver-application-and-installation-guide


Close the DdDPos and start the installation.

It should start with asking you if you want to uninstall the old driver.
Press yes to this - after this is done it will ask for a reboot of the pc.
Press reboot now.

-IMPORTANT-
When this pc starts up again after this reboot, it might start on a completely white screen (or the chosen wallpaper) with nothing else. This is just windows trying to identify the USB driver for the terminal.
Just wait a few minutes and the installer will show up for the terminal.

Follow the steps in the installer when you see this screen fill it out as shown here

Press next and finish the installation.
When installation is finished icons and start menu should reappear on the pc.

Open DdDPos
Login as a sales person
Press shotcuts followed by configure terminal

In the new window start with "download card agreements", if that succeeds run "reconciliation" if this succeds the card terminal should be ready for use. If this does not work, send to hardware

title: No reconciliation from card terminal after final checkout.
text: When a store is done for today's sale,Normally they make a cash statement on the cash register and at the end, a final report is printed from the card terminal through the receipt printer by reconciliation that shows all data for that day regarding different transactions per card type and amount. If a store contact us that they are unable to get the final receipt, In such case,the solution is to check the following settings in DdD admin for that customer. Login to DdD admin,Enter Password ddd+2016 and change the value to 1. Click save and make a reload on POS in the clerk menu.

title: "No contact"
text: If the cardterminal says no contact with POS/provider, it might mean that the terminal type is wrong in DDD Admin It doesnt happen too often, its usually missing setup on a new POS, but there has been occasions where the terminaltype would set itself to 1 instead of 10. Side note: Alot of the other typical card terminal errors can also be seen when this happens

title: In case of NETS service being down
text: If several customers are calling in about card terminal issues, NETS might be having service issues. Check: https://www.nets.eu/dk-da/Pages/driftstatus.aspx Best you can do is tell the customer to be patient and check on the website regularly. Sometimes rebooting the cardterminal can help, however there is no guarantee.

title: Setting up a new Nets terminal  (DDD)
text: ↓ This is the service card, it is used for changing the Terminal ID, if you do not have the service card, a service code can be provided by nets (it is unique for every customer), We only have one service card, so treat it with care. ↓ This is a merchant card, if you swipe the card through the terminal you will get a menu with the terminal settings/options. Every card terminal should be shipped with a merchant card. REMEMBER to pack one with the card terminal. ↓This is what a brand new card terminal looks like when turned on. First step is to give the card terminal a Terminal ID (TID). During the setup, remember to have the terminal connected to an active DDD POS, so that the card terminal can use the internet via ERC. It might be necessary to reboot the POS and terminal if an internet connection is not established. (You will find out if the card terminal has internet in a later step). ↓Swipe the service card or merchant card, and select 1. Funktion. You can navigate with the arrows and buttons (red for no, green for yes) ↓Next window is the TID, press the yellow clear button to delete the zeroes. ↓Type in the TID and confirm by pressing the green button ↓Now you need to swipe the service card, if you do not have the service card, but instead a service code, you can press the red button and then type the service code instead, then press green to confirm the service code. ↓This is the confirmation of TID being saved on the device, you might have to press green to move along. ↓Here we are back at the TID selection, you can now see that the terminal ID is saved. From here, press the red button a couple of times, the terminal will then reboot and download the new settings. ↓This is what the reboot looks like, might take a minute or two. ↓When the terminal is turned on again, you will be greeted with this. Press the green button to confirm. If you keep coming back to this window after confirming, the card terminal does not have an internet connection. Reboot the POS ↓ Make sure that the terminal is reserved to COM port 20, usually it will be named Lane300, but it can also be recognized as a generic USB device. If in doubt you can always try unplugging, and plugging in again, so see what device disappears/pops up again ↓This is what it looks like if the terminal has internet connection. It will be downloading and installing for a few minutes. ↓ When the TID settings have been downloaded, the card terminal look like this. Technically ready for use, but for good measure you can download card agreements. ↓ Swipe the merchant card, select 1, Kortaftaler ↓ Select 1 Hent aftaler ↓The terminal will download the card agreements for a couple of minutes, and then appear as below ↓ Press the green button twice to save the settings. Now the terminal is almost ready to go. You probably need to download card agreements via DDD POS and do a reconciliation as well, before the terminal is ready for use.
description:
↓ This is the service card, it is used for changing the Terminal ID, if you do not have the service card, a service code can be provided by nets (it is unique for every customer), We only have one service card, so treat it with care.  

↓ This is a merchant card, if you swipe the card through the terminal you will get a menu with the terminal settings/options. Every card terminal should be shipped with a merchant card. REMEMBER to pack one with the card terminal.



↓This is what a brand new card terminal looks like when turned on. First step is to give the card terminal a  Terminal ID (TID). During the setup, remember to have the terminal connected to an active DDD POS, so that the card terminal can use the internet via ERC. It might be necessary to reboot the POS and terminal if an internet connection is not established.  (You will find out if the card terminal has internet in a later step). 

↓Swipe the service card or merchant card, and select 1. Funktion. You can navigate with the arrows and buttons (red for no, green for yes)


↓Next window is the TID, press the yellow clear button to delete the zeroes.

↓Type in the TID and confirm by pressing the green button


↓Now you need to swipe the service card, if you do not have the service card, but instead a service code, you can press the red button and then type the service code instead, then press green to confirm the service code.  


↓This is the confirmation of TID being saved on the device, you might have to press green to move along.



↓Here we are back at the TID selection, you can now see that the terminal ID is saved. From here, press the red button a couple of times, the terminal will then reboot and download the new settings. 

↓This is what the reboot looks like, might take a minute or two.


↓When the terminal is turned on again, you will be greeted with this. Press the green button to confirm. If you keep coming back to this window after confirming, the card terminal does not have an internet connection. Reboot the POS


↓ Make sure that the terminal is reserved to COM port 20, usually it will be named Lane300, but it can also be recognized as a generic USB device. If in doubt you can always try unplugging, and plugging in again, so see what device disappears/pops up again


↓This is what it looks like if the terminal has internet connection. It will be downloading and installing for a few minutes. 


↓ When the TID settings have been downloaded, the card terminal look like this. Technically ready for use, but for good measure you can download card agreements. 


↓ Swipe the merchant card, select 1, Kortaftaler


↓ Select 1 Hent aftaler


↓The terminal will download the card agreements for a couple of minutes, and then appear as below


↓ Press the green button twice to save the settings. 


Now the terminal is almost ready to go. You probably need to download card agreements via DDD POS and do a reconciliation as well, before the terminal is ready for use.

title: Lane 3600 card terminal installation-DdD POS
text: When a DdD customer contact support team that they want to setup the new card terminal lane 3600 on DdD POS,the following procedure can be used. First ask them to check if the USB is properly connected. If you cannot see the terminal in Device Manager, this might be the problem. Inform them that a restart of the pc will happen, and this process can take up to 10mins where they can't use the POS Please note that no extra setup is needed and it is the same configuration that are being used for older model card terminals. Please note that if the customer was using ipp350 so they can use the same cable so the only thing they need to is to switch the old card terminal to the new lane 3600 terminal. Card terminal to DdD POS is always connected via a usb cable as shown in Screenshot 1. The clerk just needs to unplug the cable from the old card terminal(ipp350) and plug it in the new card terminal(L3600) as both old card terminal (ipp350) and new card terminal (L3600) has the same cable interface shown in screenshot 2. Screenshot 1: Screenshot 2: The com port in device manager must be com 20 as usual. If the store has an IPP350,then the driver needs to be updated by downloading it from the following link- https://ingenico.com/en/resources/ingenico-usb-driver-application-and-installation-guide Close the DdDPos and start the installation. It should start with asking you if you want to uninstall the old driver. Press yes to this - after this is done it will ask for a reboot of the pc. Press reboot now. -IMPORTANT- When this pc starts up again after this reboot, it might start on a completely white screen (or the chosen wallpaper) with nothing else. This is just windows trying to identify the USB driver for the terminal. Just wait a few minutes and the installer will show up for the terminal. Follow the steps in the installer as done for installation of lane 3000 terminal by selecting com 20 port. When the driver is installed,Open DdD POS program and perform download card agreement and reconciliation on the card terminal. You can also try a test transaction on the new card terminal to confirm if everything works fine as it should.
